<item>
            <title>[FLINK-19174] idleTimeMsPerSecond can report incorrect values (0 or values more than one second)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-19174</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If task is blocked for more than 60 seconds (&lt;tt&gt;org.apache.flink.metrics.MeterView#DEFAULT_TIME_SPAN_IN_SECONDS&lt;/tt&gt;), &lt;tt&gt;idleTimeMsPerSecond&lt;/tt&gt; can be reported as zero, despite task being completely idle. Once the task is unblocked and the &lt;tt&gt;idleTimeMsPerSecond&lt;/tt&gt; metric is updated, it can for the next 60 seconds exceed 1000ms/second.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average value over the longer periods of time will be correct and accurate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
